---
description: TypeScript and Vue 3 development standards
globs:
alwaysApply: agent
---

- All code must be TypeScript. No `any` types except when strictly necessary
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">` for all SFCs
- Follow Vue 3's recommended folder and naming conventions.
- Keep functions focused and manageable (under 50-75 lines).
- Use try-catch for async operations; leverage Vue 3 error utilities.
